10 An Act relating to building codes; directing the
Department of Human Services to work with the State
11 Fire Marshal to develop certain guidelines; providing
that certain child care homes shall not be denied a
12 license; prohibiting stricter requirements; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1000.31 of Title 59, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 The Department of Human Services shall work with the Oklahoma
20 State Fire Marshal to develop guidelines that allow family child
21 care homes and large child care homes, as defined in Section 402 of
22 Title 10 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to operate under the requirements
23 of the 2018 International Residential Code as adopted by the
24 Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission (OUBCC). Family child
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1847 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 care homes and large child care homes shall not be denied a license
2 to operate should they comply with the requirements of the
3 guidelines as established by the Department and the Oklahoma State
4 Fire Marshal. No agency, municipality, county, or other political
5 subdivision of this state shall place stricter fire and life safety
6 requirements than those outlined in the 2018 International
7 Residential Code as adopted by the OUBCC on family child care homes
8 and large child care homes.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
10 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
